{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You've all seen lots of articles on climate change,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and here's yet another New York Times article,"},{"time":5000,"text":"just like every other darn one you've seen."},{"time":7000,"text":"It says all the same stuff as all the other ones you've seen."},{"time":9000,"text":"It even has the same amount of headline as all the other ones you've seen."},{"time":12000,"text":"What's unusual about this one, maybe, is that it's from 1953."},{"time":16000,"text":"And the reason I'm saying this"},{"time":18000,"text":"is that you may have the idea this problem is relatively recent."},{"time":20000,"text":"That people have just sort of figured out about it, and now"},{"time":23000,"text":"with Kyoto and the Governator and people beginning to actually do something,"},{"time":26000,"text":"we may be on the road to a solution."},{"time":29000,"text":"The fact is -- uh-uh."},{"time":32000,"text":"We've known about this problem for 50 years, depending on how you count it."},{"time":37000,"text":"We have talked about it endlessly over the last decade or so."},{"time":39000,"text":"And we've accomplished close to zip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"This is the growth rate of CO2 in the atmosphere."},{"time":45000,"text":"You've seen this in various forms,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but maybe you haven't seen this one."},{"time":49000,"text":"What this shows is that the rate of growth of our emissions is accelerating."},{"time":52000,"text":"And that it's accelerating even faster"},{"time":54000,"text":"than what we thought was the worst case just a few years back."},{"time":58000,"text":"So that red line there was something that a lot of skeptics said"},{"time":61000,"text":"the environmentalists only put in the projections"},{"time":63000,"text":"to make the projections look as bad as possible,"},{"time":66000,"text":"that emissions would never grow as fast as that red line."},{"time":69000,"text":"But in fact, they're growing faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"Here's some data from actually just 10 days ago,"},{"time":74000,"text":"which shows this year's minimum of the Arctic Sea ice, and it's the lowest by far."},{"time":79000,"text":"And the rate at which the Arctic Sea ice is going away is a lot quicker than models."},{"time":84000,"text":"So despite all sorts of experts like me flying around the planet and"},{"time":87000,"text":"burning jet fuel, and politicians signing treaties --"},{"time":90000,"text":"in fact, you could argue the net effect of all this has been negative,"},{"time":93000,"text":"because it's just consumed a lot of jet fuel. (Laughter)"},{"time":96000,"text":"No, no! In terms of what we really need to do to put the brakes on"},{"time":101000,"text":"this very high inertial thing -- our big economy -- we've really hardly started."},{"time":105000,"text":"Really, we're doing this, basically. Really, not very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"I don't want to depress you too much."},{"time":114000,"text":"The problem is absolutely soluble, and even soluble in a way that's reasonably cheap."},{"time":119000,"text":"Cheap meaning sort of the cost of the military, not the cost of medical care."},{"time":124000,"text":"Cheap meaning a few percent of GDP."},{"time":128000,"text":"No, this is really important to have this sense of scale."},{"time":130000,"text":"So the problem is soluble, and the way we should go about solving it is, say,"},{"time":134000,"text":"dealing with electricity production,"},{"time":136000,"text":"which causes something like 43-or-so percent and rising of CO2 emissions."},{"time":140000,"text":"And we could do that by perfectly sensible things like conservation,"},{"time":143000,"text":"and wind power, nuclear power and coal to CO2 capture,"},{"time":147000,"text":"which are all things that are ready for giant scale deployment, and work."},{"time":152000,"text":"All we lack is the action to actually spend the money to put those into place."},{"time":157000,"text":"Instead, we spend our time talking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"But nevertheless, that's not what I'm going to talk to you about tonight."},{"time":162000,"text":"What I'm going to talk to you about tonight is stuff we might do if we did nothing."},{"time":166000,"text":"And it's this stuff in the middle here, which is what you do"},{"time":170000,"text":"if you don't stop the emissions quickly enough."},{"time":173000,"text":"And you need to deal -- somehow break the link between human actions"},{"time":176000,"text":"that change climate, and the climate change itself. And that's particularly important"},{"time":180000,"text":"because, of course, while we can adapt to climate change --"},{"time":183000,"text":"and it's important to be honest here, there will be some benefits to climate change."},{"time":186000,"text":"Oh, yes, I think it's bad. I've spent my whole life working to stop it."},{"time":189000,"text":"But one of the reasons it's politically hard is there are winners and losers -- not all losers."},{"time":193000,"text":"But, of course, the natural world, polar bears."},{"time":196000,"text":"I spent time skiing across the sea ice for weeks at a time in the high Arctic."},{"time":199000,"text":"They will completely lose."},{"time":201000,"text":"And there's no adaption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"So this problem is absolutely soluble."},{"time":204000,"text":"This geo-engineering idea, in it's simplest form, is basically the following."},{"time":207000,"text":"You could put signed particles, say sulfuric acid particles -- sulfates --"},{"time":212000,"text":"into the upper atmosphere, the stratosphere,"},{"time":214000,"text":"where they'd reflect away sunlight and cool the planet."},{"time":216000,"text":"And I know for certain that that will work."},{"time":219000,"text":"Not that there aren't side effects, but I know for certain it will work."},{"time":222000,"text":"And the reason is, it's been done."},{"time":224000,"text":"And it was done not by us, not by me, but by nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Here's Mount Pinatubo in the early '90s. That put a whole bunch of sulfur"},{"time":230000,"text":"in the stratosphere with a sort of atomic bomb-like cloud."},{"time":234000,"text":"The result of that was pretty dramatic."},{"time":237000,"text":"After that, and some previous volcanoes we have, you see"},{"time":240000,"text":"a quite dramatic cooling of the atmosphere."},{"time":242000,"text":"So this lower bar is the upper atmosphere, the stratosphere,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and it heats up after these volcanoes."},{"time":247000,"text":"But you'll notice that in the upper bar, which is the lower atmosphere"},{"time":249000,"text":"and the surface, it cools down because we shielded the atmosphere a little bit."},{"time":253000,"text":"There's no big mystery about it."},{"time":255000,"text":"There's lots of mystery in the details, and there's some bad side effects,"},{"time":258000,"text":"like it partially destroys the ozone layer -- and I'll get to that in a minute."},{"time":261000,"text":"But it clearly cools down."},{"time":263000,"text":"And one other thing: it's fast."},{"time":266000,"text":"It's really important to say. So much of the other things that we ought to do,"},{"time":269000,"text":"like slowing emissions, are intrinsically slow, because it takes time"},{"time":274000,"text":"to build all the hardware we need to reduce emissions."},{"time":277000,"text":"And not only that, when you cut emissions, you don't cut concentrations,"},{"time":280000,"text":"because concentrations, the amount of CO2 in the air,"},{"time":282000,"text":"is the sum of emissions over time."},{"time":284000,"text":"So you can't step on the brakes very quickly."},{"time":286000,"text":"But if you do this, it's quick."},{"time":288000,"text":"And there are times you might like to do something quick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291000,"text":"Another thing you might wonder about is, does it work?"},{"time":294000,"text":"Can you shade some sunlight and effectively compensate for the added CO2,"},{"time":298000,"text":"and produce a climate sort of back to what it was originally?"},{"time":301000,"text":"And the answer seems to be yes."},{"time":303000,"text":"So here are the graphs you've seen lots of times before."},{"time":306000,"text":"That's what the world looks like, under one particular climate model's view,"},{"time":309000,"text":"with twice the amount of CO2 in the air."},{"time":311000,"text":"The lower graph is with twice the amount of CO2 and 1.8 percent less sunlight,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and you're back to the original climate."},{"time":317000,"text":"And this graph from Ken Caldeira. It's important to say came, because"},{"time":320000,"text":"Ken -- at a meeting that I believe Marty Hoffart was also at in the mid-'90s --"},{"time":323000,"text":"Ken and I stood up at the back of the meeting and said,"},{"time":326000,"text":"\"Geo-engineering won't work.\""},{"time":328000,"text":"And to the person who was promoting it said,"},{"time":330000,"text":"\"The atmosphere's much more complicated.\""},{"time":332000,"text":"Gave a bunch of physical reasons why it wouldn't do a very good compensation."},{"time":335000,"text":"Ken went and ran his models, and found that it did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"This topic is also old."},{"time":340000,"text":"That report that landed on President Johnson's desk when I was two years old --"},{"time":343000,"text":"1965."},{"time":345000,"text":"That report, in fact, which had all the modern climate science --"},{"time":347000,"text":"the only thing they talked about doing was geo-engineering."},{"time":350000,"text":"It didn't even talk about cutting emissions,"},{"time":352000,"text":"which is an incredible shift in our thinking about this problem."},{"time":355000,"text":"I'm not saying we shouldn't cut emissions."},{"time":357000,"text":"We should, but it made exactly this point."},{"time":360000,"text":"So, in a sense, there's not much new."},{"time":362000,"text":"The one new thing is this essay."},{"time":364000,"text":"So I should say, I guess, that since the time of that original President Johnson report,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and the various reports of the U.S. National Academy --"},{"time":371000,"text":"1977, 1982, 1990 -- people always talked about this idea."},{"time":374000,"text":"Not as something that was foolproof, but as an idea to think about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"But when climate became, politically, a hot topic -- if I may make the pun --"},{"time":381000,"text":"in the last 15 years, this became so un-PC, we couldn't talk about it."},{"time":387000,"text":"It just sunk below the surface. We weren't allowed to speak about it."},{"time":391000,"text":"But in the last year, Paul Crutzen published this essay"},{"time":394000,"text":"saying roughly what's all been said before: that maybe, given our very slow rate"},{"time":397000,"text":"of progress in solving this problem and the uncertain impacts,"},{"time":400000,"text":"we should think about things like this."},{"time":402000,"text":"He said roughly what's been said before."},{"time":404000,"text":"The big deal was he happened to have won the Nobel prize for ozone chemistry."},{"time":407000,"text":"And so people took him seriously when he said we should think about this,"},{"time":409000,"text":"even though there will be some ozone impacts."},{"time":411000,"text":"And in fact, he had some ideas to make them go away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"There was all sorts of press coverage, all over the world,"},{"time":415000,"text":"going right down to \"Dr. Strangelove Saves the Earth,\" from the Economist."},{"time":419000,"text":"And that got me thinking. I've worked on this topic on and off,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but not so much technically. And I was actually lying in bed thinking one night."},{"time":425000,"text":"And I thought about this child's toy -- hence, the title of my talk --"},{"time":429000,"text":"and I wondered if you could use the same physics that makes that thing spin 'round"},{"time":432000,"text":"in the child's radiometer, to levitate particles into the upper atmosphere"},{"time":436000,"text":"and make them stay there."},{"time":438000,"text":"One of the problems with sulfates is they fall out quickly."},{"time":440000,"text":"The other problem is they're right in the ozone layer,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and I'd prefer them above the ozone layer."},{"time":444000,"text":"And it turns out, I woke up the next morning, and I started to calculate this."},{"time":446000,"text":"It was very hard to calculate from first principles. I was stumped."},{"time":449000,"text":"But then I found out that there were all sorts of papers already published"},{"time":452000,"text":"that addressed this topic because it happens already in the natural atmosphere."},{"time":455000,"text":"So it seems there are already fine particles"},{"time":457000,"text":"that are levitated up to what we call the mesosphere, about 100 kilometers up,"},{"time":461000,"text":"that already have this effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"I'll tell you very quickly how the effect works."},{"time":465000,"text":"There are a lot of fun complexities"},{"time":467000,"text":"that I'd love to spend the whole evening on, but I won't."},{"time":469000,"text":"But let's say you have sunlight hitting some particle and it's unevenly heated."},{"time":472000,"text":"So the side facing the sun is warmer; the side away, cooler."},{"time":474000,"text":"Gas molecules that bounce off the warm side"},{"time":477000,"text":"bounce away with some extra velocity because it's warm."},{"time":481000,"text":"And so you see a net force away from the sun."},{"time":483000,"text":"That's called the photophoretic force."},{"time":485000,"text":"There are a bunch of other versions of it that I and some collaborators"},{"time":489000,"text":"have thought about how to exploit."},{"time":491000,"text":"And of course, we may be wrong --"},{"time":493000,"text":"this hasn't all been peer reviewed, we're in the middle of thinking about it --"},{"time":495000,"text":"but so far, it seems good."},{"time":497000,"text":"But it looks like we could achieve long atmospheric lifetimes --"},{"time":500000,"text":"much longer than before -- because they're levitated."},{"time":503000,"text":"We can move things out of the stratosphere into the mesosphere,"},{"time":505000,"text":"in principle solving the ozone problem."},{"time":508000,"text":"I'm sure there will be other problems that arise."},{"time":510000,"text":"Finally, we could make the particles migrate to over the poles,"},{"time":513000,"text":"so we could arrange the climate engineering so it really focused on the poles."},{"time":517000,"text":"Which would have minimal bad impacts in the middle of the planet,"},{"time":520000,"text":"where we live, and do the maximum job of what we might need to do,"},{"time":524000,"text":"which is cooling the poles in case of planetary emergency, if you like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"This is a new idea that's crept up that may be, essentially,"},{"time":530000,"text":"a cleverer idea than putting sulfates in."},{"time":532000,"text":"Whether this idea is right or some other idea is right,"},{"time":536000,"text":"I think it's almost certain we will"},{"time":538000,"text":"eventually think of cleverer things to do than just putting sulfur in."},{"time":541000,"text":"That if engineers and scientists really turned their minds to this,"},{"time":544000,"text":"it's amazing how we can affect the planet."},{"time":547000,"text":"The one thing about this is it gives us extraordinary leverage."},{"time":551000,"text":"This improved science and engineering will, whether we like it or not,"},{"time":554000,"text":"give us more and more leverage to affect the planet,"},{"time":557000,"text":"to control the planet,"},{"time":559000,"text":"to give us weather and climate control -- not because we plan it,"},{"time":563000,"text":"not because we want it, just because science delivers it to us bit by bit,"},{"time":566000,"text":"with better knowledge of the way the system works"},{"time":568000,"text":"and better engineering tools to effect it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"Now, suppose that space aliens arrived."},{"time":576000,"text":"Maybe they're going to land at the U.N. headquarters down the road here,"},{"time":578000,"text":"or maybe they'll pick a smarter spot --"},{"time":580000,"text":"but suppose they arrive and they give you a box."},{"time":583000,"text":"And the box has two knobs."},{"time":587000,"text":"One knob is the knob for controlling global temperature."},{"time":589000,"text":"Maybe another knob is a knob for controlling CO2 concentrations."},{"time":591000,"text":"You might imagine that we would fight wars over that box."},{"time":595000,"text":"Because we have no way to agree about where to set the knobs."},{"time":598000,"text":"We have no global governance."},{"time":600000,"text":"And different people will have different places they want it set."},{"time":602000,"text":"Now, I don't think that's going to happen. It's not very likely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"But we're building that box."},{"time":610000,"text":"The scientists and engineers of the world"},{"time":612000,"text":"are building it piece by piece, in their labs."},{"time":614000,"text":"Even when they're doing it for other reasons."},{"time":616000,"text":"Even when they're thinking they're just working on protecting the environment."},{"time":619000,"text":"They have no interest in crazy ideas like engineering the whole planet."},{"time":621000,"text":"They develop science that makes it easier and easier to do."},{"time":625000,"text":"And so I guess my view on this is not that I want to do it -- I do not --"},{"time":628000,"text":"but that we should move this out of the shadows and talk about it seriously."},{"time":633000,"text":"Because sooner or later, we'll be confronted with decisions about this,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and it's better if we think hard about it,"},{"time":639000,"text":"even if we want to think hard about reasons why we should never do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"I'll give you two different ways to think about this problem that are the beginning"},{"time":649000,"text":"of my thinking about how to think about it."},{"time":651000,"text":"But what we need is not just a few oddballs like me thinking about this."},{"time":654000,"text":"We need a broader debate."},{"time":656000,"text":"A debate that involves musicians, scientists, philosophers, writers,"},{"time":660000,"text":"who get engaged with this question about climate engineering"},{"time":663000,"text":"and think seriously about what its implications are."},{"time":666000,"text":"So here's one way to think about it,"},{"time":668000,"text":"which is that we just do this instead of cutting emissions because it's cheaper."},{"time":672000,"text":"I guess the thing I haven't said about this is, it is absurdly cheap."},{"time":675000,"text":"It's conceivable that, say, using the sulfates method or this method I've come up with,"},{"time":679000,"text":"you could create an ice age at a cost of .001 percent of GDP."},{"time":685000,"text":"It's very cheap. We have a lot of leverage."},{"time":688000,"text":"It's not a good idea, but it's just important. (Laughter)"},{"time":690000,"text":"I'll tell you how big the lever is: the lever is that big."},{"time":694000,"text":"And that calculation isn't much in dispute."},{"time":697000,"text":"You might argue about the sanity of it, but the leverage is real. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"So because of this, we could deal with the problem"},{"time":707000,"text":"simply by stopping reducing emissions,"},{"time":712000,"text":"and just as the concentrations go up, we can increase"},{"time":714000,"text":"the amount of geo-engineering."},{"time":716000,"text":"I don't think anybody takes that seriously."},{"time":719000,"text":"Because under this scenario, we walk further and further away"},{"time":721000,"text":"from the current climate."},{"time":723000,"text":"We have all sorts of other problems, like ocean acidification"},{"time":725000,"text":"that come from CO2 in the atmosphere, anyway."},{"time":728000,"text":"Nobody but maybe one or two very odd folks really suggest this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"But here's a case which is harder to reject."},{"time":733000,"text":"Let's say that we don't do geo-engineering, we do what we ought to do,"},{"time":737000,"text":"which is get serious about cutting emissions."},{"time":739000,"text":"But we don't really know how quickly we have to cut them."},{"time":742000,"text":"There's a lot of uncertainty about exactly how much climate change is too much."},{"time":745000,"text":"So let's say that we work hard, and we actually don't just tap the brakes,"},{"time":748000,"text":"but we step hard on the brakes and really reduce emissions"},{"time":751000,"text":"and eventually reduce concentrations."},{"time":753000,"text":"And maybe someday -- like 2075, October 23 --"},{"time":758000,"text":"we finally reach that glorious day where concentrations have peaked"},{"time":761000,"text":"and are rolling down the other side."},{"time":763000,"text":"And we have global celebrations, and we've actually started to -- you know,"},{"time":766000,"text":"we've seen the worst of it."},{"time":769000,"text":"But maybe on that day we also find that the Greenland ice sheet"},{"time":773000,"text":"is really melting unacceptably fast, fast enough to put meters of sea level on"},{"time":779000,"text":"the oceans in the next 100 years,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and remove some of the biggest cities from the map."},{"time":783000,"text":"That's an absolutely possible scenario."},{"time":785000,"text":"We might decide at that point that even though geo-engineering was uncertain"},{"time":788000,"text":"and morally unhappy, that it's a lot better than not geo-engineering."},{"time":793000,"text":"And that's a very different way to look at the problem."},{"time":795000,"text":"It's using this as risk control, not instead of action."},{"time":798000,"text":"It's saying that you do some geo-engineering for a little while"},{"time":801000,"text":"to take the worst of the heat off, not that you'd use it as a substitute for action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"But there is a problem with that view."},{"time":808000,"text":"And the problem is the following:"},{"time":810000,"text":"knowledge that geo-engineering is possible makes"},{"time":812000,"text":"the climate impacts look less fearsome,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and that makes a weaker commitment to cutting emissions today."},{"time":818000,"text":"This is what economists call a moral hazard."},{"time":820000,"text":"And that's one of the fundamental reasons that this problem is so hard to talk about,"},{"time":824000,"text":"and, in general, I think it's the underlying reason"},{"time":826000,"text":"that it's been politically unacceptable to talk about this."},{"time":827000,"text":"But you don't make good policy by hiding things in a drawer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"I'll leave you with three questions, and then one final quote."},{"time":834000,"text":"Should we do serious research on this topic?"},{"time":837000,"text":"Should we have a national research program that looks at this?"},{"time":840000,"text":"Not just at how you would do it better,"},{"time":842000,"text":"but also what all the risks and downsides of it are."},{"time":844000,"text":"Right now, you have a few enthusiasts talking about it, some in a positive side,"},{"time":848000,"text":"some in a negative side -- but that's a dangerous state to be in"},{"time":851000,"text":"because there's very little depth of knowledge on this topic."},{"time":854000,"text":"A very small amount of money would get us some."},{"time":856000,"text":"Many of us -- maybe now me -- think we should do that."},{"time":859000,"text":"But I have a lot of reservations."},{"time":861000,"text":"My reservations are principally about the moral hazard problem,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and I don't really know how we can best avoid the moral hazard."},{"time":868000,"text":"I think there is a serious problem: as you talk about this,"},{"time":870000,"text":"people begin to think they don't need to work so hard to cut emissions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"Another thing is, maybe we need a treaty."},{"time":877000,"text":"A treaty that decides who gets to do this."},{"time":880000,"text":"Right now we may think of a big, rich country like the U.S. doing this."},{"time":882000,"text":"But it might well be that, in fact, if China wakes up in 2030 and realizes"},{"time":886000,"text":"that the climate impacts are just unacceptable,"},{"time":888000,"text":"they may not be very interested in our moral conversations about how to do this,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and they may just decide they'd really rather have a geo-engineered world"},{"time":896000,"text":"than a non-geo-engineered world."},{"time":899000,"text":"And we'll have no international mechanism to figure out who makes the decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"So here's one last thought, which was said much, much better"},{"time":905000,"text":"25 years ago in the U.S. National Academy report than I can say today."},{"time":909000,"text":"And I think it really summarizes where we are here."},{"time":912000,"text":"That the CO2 problem, the climate problem that we've heard about,"},{"time":915000,"text":"is driving lots of things -- innovations in the energy technologies"},{"time":917000,"text":"that will reduce emissions --"},{"time":919000,"text":"but also, I think, inevitably, it will drive us towards thinking about climate"},{"time":924000,"text":"and weather control, whether we like it or not."},{"time":927000,"text":"And it's time to begin thinking about it,"},{"time":929000,"text":"even if the reason we're thinking about it is to construct arguments"},{"time":932000,"text":"for why we shouldn't do it."},{"time":934000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}